00:06:44,558 --> 00:06:51,124
I can give a brief supplement which might go to the core of some concerns or some questions about the language.

68
00:06:51,905 --> 00:06:55,608
First, my name.

69
00:06:55,708 --> 00:06:56,629
My name is Mark Rumley.

70
00:06:56,669 --> 00:06:57,610
I'm the city solicitor.

71
00:06:57,630 --> 00:07:00,693
I reside at 50 Woodrow Avenue in Medford.

72
00:07:03,075 --> 00:07:10,805
right now, the way the state statute is, and you have to understand this in terms of state statute and local ordinance.

73
00:07:11,366 --> 00:07:15,972
The state statute says, in terms of notice, that it should be given to

74
00:07:17,318 --> 00:07:26,549
abutters to a petitioner property or abutters to abutters or those who are across the street within a 300-foot ambit.

75
00:07:26,989 --> 00:07:33,036
Now that doesn't mean under the state statute that everybody within the 300-foot ambit would receive notice.

76
00:07:33,437 --> 00:07:36,961
It just means abutters, abutters to abutters or those across the street.

77
00:07:38,905 --> 00:07:53,658
The resolution which is before you tonight would make it a requirement that locally, that in the city of Medford, notice be given to all persons, all persons, within a 400-foot ambit.

78
00:07:54,639 --> 00:08:00,645
Now, it's important to be cognizant of the fact that this is

79
00:08:02,303 --> 00:08:05,286
in excess of what's required by the state statute.

80
00:08:05,806 --> 00:08:10,590
Therefore, from a legal point of view, it would be considered directory only.

81
00:08:10,610 --> 00:08:11,971
I want to give you an example.

82
00:08:12,652 --> 00:08:13,673
The example would be this.

83
00:08:14,373 --> 00:08:28,445
If you were somebody who was, say, 300 feet away, but you were not an abutter or an abutter to an abutter or across the street, and you disagreed with a decision made by the board,

84
00:08:29,644 --> 00:08:39,929
If you appealed it, the land court would not recognize the fact that you didn't get notice because you were 300 feet away, because that's a local rule.

85
00:08:41,209 --> 00:08:45,611
So the land court would not say that that would give you the status of a party in interest.

86
00:08:45,871 --> 00:08:47,832
You would have to establish that another way.

87
00:08:48,492 --> 00:08:56,536
So when I say that the extra notice would be directory only, it doesn't mean that it wouldn't be given, because if you pass it as an ordinance,

88
00:08:57,376 --> 00:09:00,939
then the board and commission would have to implement that.

89
00:09:01,659 --> 00:09:21,132
However, what I'm saying is that if somebody appealed the decision to the courts, that would not give them an additional leg to stand on or some status that they didn't otherwise have because the state statute would control as being the only requirement that's compulsory.

90
00:09:22,273 --> 00:09:27,276
So that's essentially what this ordinance would be.

91
00:09:27,676 --> 00:09:40,623
And I have a little bit of data that I didn't have earlier this morning that I received from Mr. McDougal as to what this would mean from a substantive point of view by way of example, which I could give you if you like.

92
00:09:41,303 --> 00:09:42,164
I'll just explain it.

93
00:09:46,028 --> 00:09:50,710
Dennis McDougall is the clerk for the administrator for the ZBA.

94
00:09:51,210 --> 00:10:05,415
And just as an example of what this would mean, there's one project, I won't give the address, it's not that important, but it was the change of a property from a single family to a two family.

95
00:10:05,435 --> 00:10:06,956
It was before the Board of Appeals.

96
00:10:07,817 --> 00:10:16,248
Under the state statute, which means abutters, abutters to abutters, or those across the street, there were 10 notices that were given out.

97
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:28,463
If it were all owners within 300 feet, there were 234 people that would have to be notified because there was a condominium within that area.

98
00:10:29,584 --> 00:10:36,731
If it were 400 feet, there'd be 357 people that would have had to have been notified because of that condominium.

99
00:10:37,412 --> 00:10:40,155
Now, that's a very steep example.

100
00:10:40,775 --> 00:10:47,557
There's another one where, on a matter before the ZBA, under the law, 18 people were notified.

101
00:10:48,298 --> 00:10:51,439
If the circle was drawn at 300 feet, 38 people would be notified.

102
00:10:51,459 --> 00:10:53,760
And at 400 feet, 60 people would be notified.

103
00:10:58,883 --> 00:11:05,828
So you can see how there's an additional notice requirement if you draw the circle further out and further out.

104
00:11:05,908 --> 00:11:07,009
That's how this would work.

105
00:11:07,629 --> 00:11:13,834
So I give that to you simply for your information, but that's how this would work.

106
00:11:14,054 --> 00:11:18,257
And the condominium example is steep because obviously there are many units in a condominium.

107
00:11:20,239 --> 00:11:20,519
Thank you.

108
00:11:23,262 --> 00:11:24,002
Councilor Falco.

109
00:11:24,242 --> 00:11:25,123
Thank you, Mr. President.

110
00:11:25,923 --> 00:11:28,224
City Solicitor Rumley, if I may ask a few questions.

111
00:11:28,264 --> 00:11:33,006
So is this enforceable as far as if we were to vote for this change?

112
00:11:33,046 --> 00:11:41,630
I mean, is it enforceable as far as from, I mean, I guess you could always appeal it, but I mean, do we have any grounds to enforce this, I guess?

113
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,491
Yes, the enforceability would be this.

114
00:11:43,651 --> 00:11:47,393
It would be a requirement of the local board and commission to give that notice.

115
00:11:48,093 --> 00:11:52,814
Actually, it would be the petitioner who's going forth to make sure that that notice is given.

116
00:11:53,174 --> 00:11:59,975
For example, Mr. McDougall does the notices for the Board of Appeals, but the costs of that are borne by the petitioner.

117
00:12:00,515 --> 00:12:01,415
Is it enforceable?

118
00:12:01,855 --> 00:12:03,836
So the answer to that question is split.

119
00:12:04,356 --> 00:12:11,537
The first part of the answer is, if it's made an ordinance, then it is required that it be implemented by the local board or commission.

120
00:12:12,897 --> 00:12:17,218
However, at the state level, if there was an appeal to the courts,

121
00:12:18,517 --> 00:12:22,364
It would be informational, but not required.

122
00:12:22,945 --> 00:12:26,952
So to the degree that you would think that the state would enforce it, it would not.

123
00:12:31,136 --> 00:12:36,358
So I mean, I think it's interesting, and I think it's definitely, I definitely like notifying more people.

124
00:12:36,478 --> 00:12:37,498
I think that's a good thing.

125
00:12:38,339 --> 00:12:42,040
I just have, I guess, some concerns that there's like unintended consequences here.

126
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:49,383
So for like the local person that's trying to make a home improvement, put a deck on the back of their house, and they need a variance.

127
00:12:49,423 --> 00:12:50,984
Maybe they're too close to the property line.

128
00:12:52,244 --> 00:12:58,607
So if they have that type of a situation, that person is going to have to notify

129
00:13:00,090 --> 00:13:03,071
everyone within that 400 foot?

130
00:13:03,871 --> 00:13:06,892
Yes, if this ordinance were passed in its present form, yes.

